This paper is about improving the accuracy of a named entity recognition system for Vietnamese, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper uses regular expressions and a bidirectional inference method in a sequence labeling model, which are common techniques in NLP and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to machine learning and NLP.
